    <!-- ============================================================
         CATEGORY 1: HIGH-TENSION WIRE TRAPS
    ============================================================= -->
    <section class="card armory-category">
      <h2 id="wire-traps">High-Tension Wire Gopher Traps</h2>
      <p class="category-intro">These are my first pick on almost every job. High-tension stainless steel wire traps — the Macabee style and the Cinch style — are built for the main tunnel lines where the gopher is actually traveling. You're not hoping the gopher wanders into something. You're cutting off the freeway.</p>

      <div class="field-notes">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #222;">The Bagger's Field Notes</h3>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: #555;">"I've been bagging gophers since I was 15, and the right hardware is only half the battle."</p>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 0;">
          <li><strong>The Victor Standard:</strong> These "Easy Set" style traps are my daily drivers for main tunnel lines.</li>
          <li><strong>Humane Dispatch:</strong> If you get a leg-catch, be ready to handle it quickly — I've used a pellet gun in the past to ensure they don't suffer.</li>
          <li><strong>The Peanut Butter Trick:</strong> Don't set them dry. A small dab of peanut butter behind the trigger plate makes them commit to the spot for a guaranteed catch.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="picks-heading">Our Picks</h3>
      <div class="product-grid">

        <div class="product-card">
          <div class="product-badge badge-best">Best Overall</div>
          <h4 class="product-name">Victor Macabee Gopher Trap</h4>
          <p class="product-desc">The original high-tension wire trap and still the most reliable tool in the kit. Sets fast, fires clean, and holds up to years of daily use. Every serious trapper has a dozen of these.</p>
          <p class="product-best-for"><strong>Best for:</strong> Main tunnel intercept on active runs — the go-to for any fresh mound situation.</p>
          <a href="https://amzn.to/4cIJ64V" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">Shop on Amazon →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="product-card">
          <div class="product-badge badge-budget">Easier to Set</div>
          <h4 class="product-name">Cinch Traps (Scissor-Jaw)</h4>
          <p class="product-desc">A scissor-jaw design that many people find easier to arm and less prone to accidental misfires during placement. Works the same tunnel-intercept principle as the Victor but with a different trigger geometry.</p>
          <p class="product-best-for"><strong>Best for:</strong> Beginners, or anyone who finds the Victor wire mechanism fiddly to set consistently.</p>
          <a href="https://amzn.to/4sMH5cR" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">Shop on Amazon →</a>
        </div>

      </div>

