    <!-- ============================================================
         CATEGORY 2: GOPHER GASSERS & BURROW FUMIGATION
    ============================================================= -->
    <section class="card armory-category">
      <h2 id="gassers">Gopher Gassers & Burrow Fumigation</h2>
      <p class="category-intro">When you've got a deep, branching tunnel network and traps aren't producing — gassers are the move. I've used them when a gopher has gone dormant or when I'm dealing with a complex system where I can't pinpoint the active run. The key is sealing every exit hole before you light one, or you're just fumigating your lawn for nothing.</p>
      <p class="category-intro">For a full step-by-step on burrow fumigation, see the <a href="/methods/carbon-monoxide">Carbon Monoxide Burrow Treatment guide</a>.</p>

      <div class="field-notes">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #222;">The Bagger's Field Notes</h3>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: #555;">"Gassers are not a substitute for trapping — they're a supplement for when the tunnel system is too deep or spread out to work efficiently with mechanical sets."</p>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 0;">
          <li><strong>Seal everything first:</strong> Walk the yard and plug every mound opening before you light a gasser. One open exit and you've wasted the fumigation.</li>
          <li><strong>Wet soil helps:</strong> After a rain or irrigation cycle, the soil compacts better and holds the gas longer.</li>
          <li><strong>Don't use near occupied structures</strong> — CO travels underground and can seep up indoors.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="picks-heading">Our Picks</h3>
      <div class="product-grid">

        <div class="product-card">
          <div class="product-badge badge-best">Best Overall</div>
          <h4 class="product-name">Gopher Gassers (Fumigation Cartridges)</h4>
          <p class="product-desc">The standard cartridge-style gasser — light the fuse, drop it into the main run, and seal the hole. Fast to deploy and effective on mid-depth systems. The go-to fumigation option for most yards.</p>
          <p class="product-best-for"><strong>Best for:</strong> Mid-depth tunnel systems where the main run is accessible but traps aren't producing results.</p>
          <a href="https://amzn.to/4b4oF11" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">Shop on Amazon →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="product-card">
          <div class="product-badge badge-budget">Deep Systems</div>
          <h4 class="product-name">CO Burrow Treatment Device</h4>
          <p class="product-desc">Carbon monoxide-based fumigation that pushes gas deep into branching tunnel networks. More thorough penetration than standard cartridges on complex or multi-gopher systems. Higher cost per use but more complete coverage.</p>
          <p class="product-best-for"><strong>Best for:</strong> Established infestations with deep, branching runs where cartridge gassers aren't reaching the full system.</p>
          <a href="https://amzn.to/47l872T" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">Shop on Amazon →</a>
        </div>

      </div>

